te Play should really be called Remote Look or Remote Listen, because it only allows you to access media (music, pictures, videos) stored on your PS3, not play its games through your PSP. The RSS menu has also been given a small tweak, now boasting an RSS Channel Guide, for the RSS n00bs out there. If you've got wireless internet you can update your PSP directly by going to the Update System option on the XMB. Otherwise you can download it straight from Sony , and transfer the file to your PSP via USB cable. Read all 2 comments PSP firmware updated for new PS3 features PSP gets voice and video call features New PSP "definitely" coming, says "analyst" Allard admits defeat, wears dreads over PSP bet Sony's PSP Camera next month MGS4 not confirmed for 360 PSP firmware updated for new PS3 features Hackers break 360 lockout Ubisoft admits its Wii "mistakes" &copy; Future Publishing Limited. Reg No. 2008885 England. 30 Monmouth Street, Bath, BA1 2BW.
