http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/12i-0&fd=R&url=http://blog.wired.com/gadgets/2007/05/psp_firmware_up.html&cid=1116842054&ei=muxeRqqvDIX20AHe4M3QDQ Gadget Lab - Wired Blogs &laquo; Rumor Roundup: Seven iPhone Rumors Phonograph CD Player: A Generation Spanning Hack &raquo; PSP Firmware Update. Stream Content Over the Internet 8:18:13 AM If you have both a PS3 and a PSP (with the latest 1.80 ), today is your lucky day! Sony have released the 3.5 firmware update for the Playstation Portable, which will allow you to take advantage of the new streaming features, previously only available on a local network. You can now stream music, video and photos over the internet from your home machine using the service called Remote Play. Several picture quality settings are available, so you can adjust according to available bandwidth. After applying the update, you'll need to hook the two consoles together via USB for a certification process, which means that when you are out and about, your PS3 will know it's you calling in from the cloud. There is also an update to the PSPs RSS news reader, adding a channel guide. What are you waiting for? Go! The contents on PS3 through the net You are currently signed in as 7-Hour Battery Life Claim For Raon Everun Handheld PC iTunes Stashes Your Name in DRM-Free Downloads Samsung's i620 Is In Our Future Invasion of The Crazy Watches Phonograph CD Player: A Generation Spanning Hack PSP Firmware Update. Stream Content Over the Internet Rumor Roundup: Seven iPhone Rumors Video:The Impossible Insides of a Working Hard Drive Wall Gear Clock Exposes its Inner Workings Fujitsu F904i: Widescreen Phone for ADD Sufferers Review: Duel Systems DuelAdapterâDouble Your Connection Pleasure Review: Audio-Technica ATH-ANC7â Pure Noise Canceling Bliss Review: Helio OceanâWaves of Innovation Review: Craftsman 4.0Vâ The Only Thing it Screws is You Review: Black & Deckerâs 3.6V Firestormâ Trying to Hang with the Big Boys Review: Hitachi DB3D