 it to reduce parts-procurement costs by at least 10 percent, the paper said. . All rights reserved. More from News.com on this story's topics Create an email alert Create an email alert Create an email alert Create an email alert May 29, 2007, 4:06 AM PDT May 28, 2007, 11:01 PM PDT Read more comments > Photos: On the road to Microsoft's Milan In all, Microsoft built more than 85 early prototypes for a tabletop computer. Here are two of them. AMD shows sunny side of Barcelona AMD warns of revenue shortfall Intel, AMD vie for server attention Dented Dell picks up AMD chips amid SEC probe Get this story's "Big Picture" > PC maker displays cooling system and more Advanced Micro Devices demos new ATI Radeon HD 2900 "Internet 2.0" will create a shift away from PCs, Zander says Watch more videos > Get more news around the Web with News.com Extra > Top picks from News.com readers Toshiba to use AMD chip in laptop PCs AMD goes quad-core with Phenom AMD shows sunny side of Barcelona AMD's new Puma stalking Intel's Centrino Intel: Software needs to heed Moore's Law Microsoft hopes 'Milan' table PC has magic touch FAQ: 21st-century guide to indoor lighting Intel's chipset road map lacks a driver Vista draining laptop batteries, patience Intel's new Centrino for work and play Market news, charts, SEC filings, and more Grads and dads gift guide Get CNET's gadget gift picks for the dad who has everything and the grad who TVs and home theater Popular on CNET Networks: Copyright &copy;2007 CNET Networks, Inc. All rights reserved.
