http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/9-0&fd=R&url=http://www.dnaindia.com/report.asp%3FNewsID%3D1100242&cid=1116803829&ei=jv1eRobJFYXoqgPDpanNDQ DNA - Evolutions - Russian cosmonauts complete five-hour spacewalk - Daily News & Analysis Open in new window Russian cosmonauts complete five-hour spacewalk Thursday, IST To reprint this article, contact HOUSTON: Two Russian cosmonauts Commander Fyodor Yurchikhin and Flight Engineer Oleg Kotov successfully completed a five-hour, 25-minute spacewalk from the Pirs docking compartment airlock while Indian American astronaut Sunita Williams provided support aboard the international space station. The Russian astronauts undertook the spacewalk installing Service Module Debris Protection (SMDP) panels and rerouting a Global Positioning System antenna cable. Wednesday's spacewalk marks the first spacewalk for both Yurchikhin and Kotov. Additional SMDP panels will be installed on Zvezda during a second spacewalk on June six. During that spacewalk Yurchikhin and Kotov also will install a section of an Ethernet cable on the Zarya module and a Russian experiment called Biorisk on Pirs. Six SMDPs from bundle No 1 were installed during an August 16, 2002, spacewalk by Expedition 5 Commander Valery Korzun and Flight Engineer Peggy Whitson. Those SMDPs were delivered to the station by Endeavour during STS-111 in June 2002. The remaining three bundles and their adaptor were delivered by Discovery during STS-116 last December and attached to PMA-3 by spacewalkers Bob Curbeam and Sunita Williams. Williams was intra vehicular officer for yesterday's spacewalk, advising and keeping the space walkers on schedule. After the installation task, the space walkers moved back to Pirs and into the airlock. Hatch closure marking the end of the spacewalk was at 8:30 pm. More articles in Evolutions &#187; Google to make Web work offline Italian doctor builds vaginal tissue in lab VSNL launches WiMax services in Bangalore Be the first (This name wi