pen source opens up more choices and gives them something to use as a bargaining chip with proprietary software vendors. Companies are also becoming more comfortable with subscription revenue as a business model, something common among open source companies, while larger enterprises are also getting on board. Financial backing from venture capitalists is helping boost growth, IDC said. Software distribution is growing, but revenues will take longer to follow suit, researchers found. That's partly because much open source software is free, while other products use a subscription revenue model rather than getting users to pay a lump sum up front. / 1000 max characters Brits are Busiest Surfers Microsoft Accused of Endangering Users Mobile Devices Set Record Gartner Cuts Chips Forecast Xandros Joins Novell in Licensing Microsoft IP Linux distributor agrees to licensing deal similar to the one Novell struck with Microsoft last year. Brits are Busiest Surfers People in the U.K. spend more time online than the rest of Europe or the U.S., a new study finds. Microsoft Accused of Endangering Users Internet user profiling could help repressive regimes identify dissidents, group warns. LANDesk Offers Free Trial Tech management software for ThinkVantage is available for evaluation through Lenovo. Sneaky Hack Ducks Detection A new, stealthy attack serves up malicious code only once, making it harder to spot and track. Receive the latest reviews, how-to's, news, and more. Product Tips & Reviews PC World's Free Whitepapers Enter your trial subscription and get 2 Risk-Free Issues plus Bonus CD-ROM . If you like , pay just $19.97 for 10 more issues (12 in all). Otherwise, write "cancel" on the bill, return it, and owe nothing. You will also get Weekly Brief, a free e-mail newsletter. I would like to receive occasional e-mails about special offers and information from carefully screened companies. LCD wide screen monitors &copy; 1998-2007, PC World Communications, Inc. Terms of Servi