ght, although the appearance of any Zelda title sometimes seems to make the gaming masses forget that). The other reason is the fact that Nintendo's hardware production has been vastly improved since April, resulting in even higher sales. These figures will only look worse for Sony in the next few months if they don't get something worthwhile out the door pronto. News: Nintendo getting WLAN routers for the Wii? News: Analyst: Wii shortages may continue to holiday 2007, Sony cuts back PS3 production News: Nintendo anticipates over 50% of the U.S. market share : Pokemon Battle Revolution : Mortal Kombat Armageddon : Big Brain Academy: Wii Degree : Rayman Raving Rabbids 2 Wii outgunning PS3 5-to-1 in Japan Stranglehold Q&A: Multiplayer a go, late summer release confirmed Halo 3 puts the pressure on GTA IV New media content heading to Xbox Live Marketplace HALO 3: July 2007 GamePro cover image revealed Subscribe to GamePro Magazine In the Current Issue Give a Gift of &copy;2006 IDG Entertainment. All rights reserved. Terms Of Service Agreement
