ids and go someplace safe for a few days. When Tony told Carm Bobby was dead, Carm didn&#8217;t even come close to crying, which is out of character for her character. Think back to anytime she heard someone was killed and she was always the first to scream and/or cry. And yet Bobby was her brother-in-law and she had no reaction to being told he was dead. Too strange. While Tony is with Carm, Patsy and Sylvio are shot. Patsy runs away, but Syl is left for dead by the hitman. Syl is in the hospital in a coma and not expected to wake up. Carm and Meadow stop by to see Janice, (where was A.J.?) and Tony and Paulie along with Tony&#8217;s driver and another guy go to a safe house. It ended with Tony lying down in bed with the gun Bobby gave him in the first episode of this season. The camera did a visceral move, as if trying to make you think someone was closing in on Tony. Will Tony get whacked next week? Will Paulie betray Tony? Will the Arabs Tony turned in to the FBI turn out to be terrorists and Tony will save us from them? Will Dr. Melfi be back? Will Syl live? Will A.J. die? Three Earthquakes Rattle New Hampshire Posted by admin in (Monday June 4, 2007 at Portsmouth - Three mild earthquakes struck New Hampshire this past weekend, according to media reports Monday. Two earthquakes struck Saturday night and another Sunday afternoon near the Portsmouth-Exeter area. Although the quakes rattled some buildings, no major damage has been reported. Initially, investigators thought the earthquakes were caused by methane gas explosions. The found areas where gas was escaping from underground near Portsmouth late Saturday evening. Assistant Fire Chief Steven Achilles says that they have ruled out any explosions and believe that the event is linked to seismic activity reported by emergency management officials. Achilles says the methane may be a result of the earthquakes. Angelina Jolie Down To 100lbs U.S. Rep. William Jefferson Indicted Boeing 737 Makes Emergency Landing In 