http://www.physorg.com/news100193690.html&cid Toshiba Brings Worlds First Slim HD DVD Re-writable Drive to Notebook PCs Space & Earth science Published: 40 minutes ago, 16:34 EST, Toshiba Brings Worlds First Slim HD DVD Re-writable Drive to Notebook PCs Toshiba today announced the worlds first slim HD DVD-RW drive for notebook PCs that can read and write and rewrite to HD DVD-RW discs, and read and write to HD DVD-R discs and to standard DVD and CD discs. Sample shipments of the new drive are scheduled to start next month. The new SD-L912A makes it possible to backup the large capacities of PC hard drives to the reusable format of HD DVD-RW discs, and store data-rich HD digital content. The drives ability to rewrite to HD DVD-RW also opens the way to a wide range of applications involving storage and rewriting of large volumes of data. The new product also supports high speed read and write for standard DVD and CD discs, and the complete library of different DVD and CD formats. The new drive is compliant with the EU RoHS directive on environmentally hazardous substances, which came into force in July 2006. Toshiba will feature the new drive at Computex 2007, which will be held in Taipei, Taiwan from June 5 to 9. » Next Article in Electronic Devices - Hardware: YouTube videos to play on Apple TV would you recommend this story? 1 vote(s) so far; rank not shown You need to be registered at PhysOrgForum to add your comments. If you do not have a username / password please Registration is very simple and will not take much time! Suggest a story idea DVD+RW 8X to be the World's Fastest DVD Rewriting HP Adding HD-DVD/Blu-ray Hybrid Drives to PCs Pioneer Announced Blu-ray Disc Combination Drive Dell Offers Solid State Drives on Select Notebooks Sprint's WiMAX Future Is Open New Concept Video Camera for SDHC Memory Card Recording Toshiba Brings HD DVD Write Drive to Desktop PCs Toshiba Unveils World's First Slim HD DVD Write Drive for Notebook PCs A Company by Name Add h