nd improving the company's prospects for [the next financial year]," Pachter said. Pachter added that such a delay may not be motivated solely by financial calendaring, but that extra space in the release gap could also could serve to give gamers a bit more time to refill their coffers after the release, which features two , consumers on a budget may be forced to choose between these two high profile games this fall. Have a Xbox 360 question? Keep in mind that this is only analyst speculation, but even if it were confirmed to be true, it wouldn't necessarily be considered a bad thing. After all, it gives Rockstar more time to tweak the game, and allows gamers a chance to take a breather between both blockbuster titles, which will undoubtedly release at the hefty price tag of $60 or more. And if it happens to help Take Two impress its investors by vastly improving their 2008 portfolio, then so be it. Rockstar announces a Special Edition for GTA IV SURPRISE: Bungie announces early Halo 3 ship date -- September... Three editions of Halo 3 planned : Medal of Honor: Airborne : Left 4 Dead : Need for Speed ProStreet : Grand Theft Auto IV : Forza Motorsport 2 Wii outgunning PS3 5-to-1 in Japan Stranglehold Q&A: Multiplayer a go, late summer release confirmed Halo 3 puts the pressure on GTA IV New media content heading to Xbox Live Marketplace HALO 3: July 2007 GamePro cover image revealed Subscribe to GamePro Magazine In the Current Issue Give a Gift of &copy;2006 IDG Entertainment. All rights reserved. Terms Of Service Agreement
