diately respond to the attorney general's comments. Mr. Frederiksen said the attorney general believes MySpace is overstepping its authority. âThe last time I checked, we were the law enforcement agency, not them,â he said. for Internet & Society Executive Director John Palfrey said MySpace is being a good corporate citizen as it tries to navigate the âincredibly murkyâ waters of the ECPA. âI think that MySpace is doing absolutely the right thing in being extremely cautious about the privacy of its users,â Mr. Palfrey said. âThe job of the attorney general is to request the information that it needs to prosecute wrongdoers under the law,â he said. âI think the appropriate tug of war that occurs is between the prosecutor who wants as much as possible and the company that wants to protect its users, where they are innocent.â The attorney general filed a response to MySpaceâs request late Monday afternoon, but his office woudl not immediately provide details. Keibi Aims to Police UGC Startup raises $6M in second round funding. MySpace Settles on Spam Social networking company gets $2.55 million in cash from The Globe.com. ChinaCache Rings Up $31.5M Redeye VC Talks Valuation Inflation Keibi Aims to Police UGC Could not find the linkURL in the DB: /Article.aspx?a=22486&hed=Pennsylvania+AG+Slaps+MySpace&sector=Industries&subsector=InternetAndServices. Letter from the Editor &copy; 1993-2006 Red Herring, Inc. All rights reserved.
http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/2-3&fd=R&url=http://www.newsfactor.com/story.xhtml%3Fstory_id%3D0100010VZY1I&cid=1116948986&ei=h4BkRvOzHJGoqwPdn5maBg NewsFactor Network | Sony Slashes Blu-ray Player Prices News & Information for Technology Purchasers Maximize your BPM Investment: Need help taming your data? Sony Slashes Blu-ray Player Prices June 4, 2007 9:21AM With Sony's decision to slash the price of the BDP-300 Blu-ray player -- likely a response to Toshiba's lower-cost HD DVD players -- some are now speculating about whether the PS3 will see price drops in the coming weeks. The PlayStation 3 comes with a built-in Blu-ray player, which was partially to blame for the console's delayed ship dates. Open Source a $6B Industry by 2011 Microsoft, Xandros Sign Patent Deal China Puts Moratorium on Internet Cafes RealPlayer Offers One-Click Downloads Study Finds 4 Percent of Links Malicious Sony is slashing the price of its new BDP-300 Blu-ray disc player, which will be available in retail outlets for $499. That's $100 less than originally announced. In fact, just six months since its market debut, Sony has cut the price of its Blu-ray player from $999 to $499, a 50 percent reduction that took traditional DVD players about two years, according to Envisioneering Group data. When DVD players launched about 10 years ago, the price tag was $1,000. A year later, it was still $800. Two years later, retail cost finally dropped to $500. Sony's advantage is that it manufacturers its own blue laser diodes, a key part of the next-gen players. "Sony is passing on some of the manufacturing savings to customers," said Richard Doherty, an analyst at Envisioneering Group. "The inability to manufacturer enough diodes was a headache for the PS3 last winter, but now Sony has enough to allow these half-price players." Sony's decision to slash the price might be a response to rival Toshiba's retail rebates. Toshiba uses the competing HD DVD format in its players. The companies are engaged in a bitter battle over which standard will reign supreme in the market. Banking on subsidies to help get its HD DVD players into consumers' living rooms, Toshiba is offering its players for $399. Most retailers offer a $100 rebate, and Amazon offers the machine for $249 through a special deal with Toshiba. But, Doherty said, Toshiba is losing money whereas Sony is making money on its $499 player. "We should see prices stay steady for some time," Doherty said. "I expect there will be some Black Friday discounts and we'll see some fall products from Sony's competitors. We'll see Samsung, LG, and others come close to Sony, but they aren't able to make their own blue laser diodes so they may have higher costs than Sony." Will the PS3 Follow? Some are speculating about whether the PlayStation 3 will see price drops in the coming weeks. However, most analysts don't expect the PS3 to follow the BDP-300's lead. Sony might be waiting to see what does with its Xbox 360. "We think Microsoft is just about break-even with the Xbox and that Sony is at the break-even point this summer," Doherty said. "The PS3 delivers more in its package, though. If you wanted to get an equivalent to the PS3 on the Xbox side it would cost $670 because you would have to add on the HD DVD drive. So until there's some discounting from Microsoft, we don't except Sony to discount." Envisioneering research shows the PlayStation 3 is selling at a faster rate six months after launch than the PlayStation 2 did. While the PlayStation 3 is often compared to Nintendo's Wii, which is half the price, Doherty said the battle between next-generation consoles is clearly between Sony and Microsoft. Forrester applies their Total Economic Impact model to assess the value of Managed Security Services to a multibillion dollar international media company. View Forrester's Study on MSS offered to you by SecureWorks New Era Dawning in Mobile Computing Virtualization Cutting Storage Costs How Flash Memory Will Change PCs Palm's Foleo: Measuring the Impact Samsung Debuts 4-GB Mobile Chipset OLPC Laptop Caught in the Crossfire MIT prof says Intel undermining effort. Palm's Foleo: Measuring the Impact Initial reaction mainly disappointment. Staples Starts PC Recycle Program Can be dropped off for a $10 fee. Product Information and Resources for Technology You Can Use To Boost Your Business Maximize your BPM Investment: The BPA Imperative. From Workpoint Experience CRM Success with Salesforce.com. Free Trial - the affordable high end CRM solution from TechExcel. Do more, travel less with GoToMeeting  Online Meetings Made Easy Learn about the software-based VoIP solution from Microsoft. Tame data with the HP StorageWorks All-in-One Storage System. VeriSign EV SSL Certificates are the most trusted option for SSL. Tame data with the HP StorageWorks All-in-One Storage System. Compare Windows Server to Linux Microsoft System Center: A family of leading IT management solutions ITIL provides the foundation for quality IT service management Please take a survey for a chance to win $500! Minimize spam threats to your communications infrastructure Learn more about Microsoft Forefront. It makes defending your systems easier. View Forresters Study on MSS offered to you by SecureWorks. Learn more about HP MFPs at www.hp.com/go/considerhpmfp London Stock Exchange chooses Windows over Linux for Reliability. Compare Windows Server to Linux Learn more about Microsoft Forefront. It makes defending your systems easier. Microsoft System Center - Enterprise-class reliability, scalability, and security. Learn about the software-based VoIP solution from Microsoft. Secure mobile devices and data. Free trial from Sybase iAnywhere. VeriSign EV SSL Certificates are the most trusted option for SSL. SecureWorks offers you Forrester's Study on MSS. McAfee Study Finds 4 Percent of Search Results Malicious Using several automated techniques, a SiteAdvisor study determined that 4 percent of the query results