http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/9-3&fd=R&url=http://www.allheadlinenews.com/articles/7007539705&cid=1116967459&ei=h4BkRvOzHJGoqwPdn5maBg AHN | Apple Announces U.S. Launch-Date For iPhone - June 29 | June 4, 2007 global news for the digital world Apple Announces U.S. Launch-Date For iPhone - June 29 June 4, 2007 8:35 a.m. EST Jacob Cherian - AHN News Writer Cupertino, CA (AHN) - Apple has finally revealed its much-anticipated launch date for its revolutionary iPhone. The date will be June 29 in the U.S. A release date for Europe and for other parts of the world has yet to be determined. That date was broadcast on a number of TV ads on Sunday, and later confirmed by Apple. The ads also mentioned that the phone will be available "only on the new AT&T," BBC news reported. Depending on the favored configuration, the iPhone will sell of $499 or $599. The device is presumably more advanced than other smart-phones and is described as a cell phone plus a personal digital assistant. As a matter of fact, Apple CEO Steve Jobs supposedly can't leave home without it. He said that he was carrying his iPhone on him during last week's "public conversation" with friend and rival Bill Gates of Microsoft at the D5: All Things Digital Conference in California. The most impressive feature that the device touts is its touch screen-interface. And this is likely to pave the way for more smart-phones to add on this feature, say experts. Just last week, a computer in a coffee table design that uses touch screen-interface was outed by Microsoft, called "Surface." Some of the functions on the iPhone include surfing the Net, watching videos and going through your email using your finger as a pointer. Apple is hoping the iPhone' s compatibility with iTunes music and video store will appeal to its customers, who are already hooked to the iPod. The Cupertino, California-based firm is also attempting to enter the mobile phone market, which is far more lucrative than the MP3 market. The iPhone's release has been long-awaited by Apple watchers since its announcement in January at the San Francisco MacWorld, stealing the limelight from the Consumers Electronics Show, held simultaneously in Las Vegas. Copyright © AHN Media Corp - All rights reserved. Redistribution, republication. syndication, rewriting or broadcast is expressly prohibited without the prior written consent of AHN. © 2007 by AHN Media Corp.
